cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a POI selection scheme and incorporates it into XGBoost to achieve more accurate estimation results. This involves the use of machine learning techniques.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper analyzes the implicit relationships between the points of Interest (POI) and the supply-demand gap in the context of Didi, an online car-hailing service. This involves the retrieval of relevant information from the data.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with the optimization of the vehicle utilization in an online car-hailing service, which involves the analysis of the social and information networks of the passengers and drivers.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the impact of the online car-hailing service on the society, particularly in terms of improving the overall user experience.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a method to improve the supply-demand estimation in an online car-hailing service, which involves the control of the system to minimize the waiting time of passengers and optimize the vehicle utilization.
